    "client_msg_id": "544DA75C-6A92-4E1F-91C4-7133DA010517",
    "text": "One thing I loved about phpbb etc. was the possibility to organize by topics but also the ability to view a chronological feed of new posts across all topics. Replying to a topic would bring it to the top of a forum and also surface in list of latest posts. \n\nWe have channels in Slack, but in Slack, threads get burried quickly. \n\n> Forums are the sections where topics are stored. Without forums, your users would have nowhere to post! Creating forums is very easy.\n<https://www.phpbb.com/support/docs/en/3.3/ug/quickstart/forums/|https://www.phpbb.com/support/docs/en/3.3/ug/quickstart/forums/>",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1720065086.549499",
    "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "3wvxa",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "One thing I loved about phpbb etc. was the possibility to organize by topics but also the ability to view a chronological feed of new posts across all topics. Replying to a topic would bring it to the top of a forum and also surface in list of latest posts. \n\n"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "We have channels in Slack"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", but in Slack, threads get burried quickly. \n\n"
              }
